

=Bio=

"Charles Wyble is a seasoned systems craftsman with a demonstrated expertise and multi disciplinary approach to the design, construction, deployment and defense of global scale systems for the worlds largest brands.

He has worked for companies spanning from small startups (StimTV, CampusExplorer) to major global brands (Intuit, The Walt Disney Company, IAC (evite.com), GSI, Fox Audience Network) and is currently employed full time by HostGator.

He has also contracted for the Department of Defense on multiple occasions and provided a wide range of IT support services to numerous small businesses throughout the greater Los Angeles area.

He is currently working on “building an alternative, open, secure, cost effective bit moving platform for tomorrows distributed, decentralized, ipv6 only default free zone”."
(http://blog.knownelement.com/about/)


